<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1986b, &ldquo;Plutarco, Ammonio e
l&rsquo;Academia,&rdquo; in F. E. Brenk and I. Gallo (eds.),
<em>Miscellanea Plutarchea</em>, Ferrara , 97&ndash;110.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1988a, &ldquo;The history of the concept of
eclecticism,&rdquo; in J. M. Dillon and A. A. Long (eds.), <em>The
Question of Eclecticism</em>, Berkeley, 5&ndash;33.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1988b, &ldquo;Science and Metaphysics.
Platonism, Aristotelianism, and Stoicism in Plutarch&rsquo;s <em>On
the Face in the Moon</em>&rdquo;, in J. M. Dillon and A. A. Long
(eds.), <em>The Question of Eclecticism</em>, Berkeley,
126&ndash;144.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, &ldquo;Platone e Aristotele nella
tradizione pitagorica secondo Plutarco,&rdquo; in <em>Plutarco, Platon
y Arist&ocirc;teles. Actas del V Congresso Internacional de la
IPS</em>, Madrid, 9&ndash;24.</li>

<li>D&ouml;rrie, H., 1971, &ldquo;Die Stellung Plutarchs im
Platonismus seiner Zeit,&rdquo; in <em>Philomathes. Studies and Essays
in the humanities in memory of Ph. Merlan</em>, The Hague,
36&ndash;56.</li>

<li>Eliasson, E., 2008, <em>The Notion of &lsquo;That which depends on
us&rsquo; in Plotinus and its bacground</em>, Leiden: Philosophia
Antiqua.</li>

<li>Ferrari, F., 1995, <em>Dio, Idee e Materia. La struttura del cosmo
in Plutarco di Cheronea</em>, Napoli: D&rsquo;Auria Editore.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996a, &ldquo;La generazione precosmica e
la struttura della materia in Plutarco,&rdquo; <em>Museum
Helveticum</em> 53: 44&ndash;55.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1996b, &ldquo;La teoria delle idee in
Plutarco,&rdquo; <em>Elenchos</em>, 17: 121&ndash;142.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001, &ldquo;La letteratura filosofica di
carattere esegetico in Plutarco,&rdquo; <em>Siculorum Gymnasium</em>,
54: 259&ndash;283.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, &ldquo;Der Gott Plutarchs und der
Gott Platons,&rdquo; in R. Hirsch&ndash;Luipold (ed.), <em>Gott und
die G&ouml;tter bei Plutarch. G&ouml;tterbilder&ndash;Weltbilder</em>,
Berlin&ndash;New York: De Gruyter, 13&ndash;25.</li>

<li>Froidefond, C., 1987, &ldquo;Plutarque et le Platonisme,&rdquo; in
<em>Aufstieg und Niedergang der r&ouml;mischen Welt</em>, II.36.1:
184&ndash;233.</li>

<li>Gill, Chr., 2006, <em>The Structured Self</em>, Oxford: Oxford
University Press.</li>

<li>Ingenkamp, H. G., 1971, <em>Plutarch Schriften &uuml;ber die
Heilung der Seele</em>, G&ouml;ttingen.</li>

<li>Jones, R. M., 1916, <em>The Platonism of Plutarch</em>, Menasha
(2nd ed. New York 1980).</li>

<li>Jones, C. P., 1966, &ldquo;Towards a Chronology of
Plutarch&rsquo;s Works,&rdquo; in <em>Journal of Roman Studies</em>,
56: 61&ndash;74.</li>

<li>Helmig, C., 2005, &ldquo;Die Weltentstehung des <em>Timaios</em>
und die platonische <em>Homoiosis The&ocirc;i</em>&mdash;Zum
kosmologischen Hintergrund von Plutarch <em>De sera numinis
vindicta</em> 550D&ndash;E,&rdquo; in Th. Leinkauf and C. Steel (ed.),
<em>Platon Timaios als Grundtext der Kosmologie in Sp&auml;tantike,
Mittelalter und Renaissance</em>, Leuven 13&ndash;35.</li>

<li>Hershbell, J., 1987, &ldquo;Plutarch&rsquo;s <em>De anima
procreatione in Timaeo</em>. An Analysis of Structure and
Content&rdquo;, in <em>Aufstieg und Niedergang der r&ouml;mischen
Welt</em>, II.36.1: 234&ndash;247.</li>

<li>Hirsch-Luipold, R. (ed.), 2005, <em>Gott und die G&ouml;tter bei
Plutarch. G&ouml;tterbilder&ndash;Weltbilder</em>, Berlin&ndash;New
York: De Gruyter.</li>

<li>Kahn, C., 2001, <em>Pythagoras and the Pythagoreans: A Brief
History</em>, Indianapolis: Hackett.</li>

<li>Karamanolis, G., 2006, <em>Plato and Aristotle in Agreement?
Platonists on Aristotle from Antiochus to Porphyry</em>, Oxford:
Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;Numenius&rdquo;, <em>The
Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy</em> (Spring 2014 edition), Edward
N. Zalta (ed.), URL =
 &lt;<a href="https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/spr2014/entries/numenius/">https://plato.stanford.edu/archives/spr2014/entries/numenius/</a>&gt;.</li>
 
<li>Kechagia, E., 2011, <em>Plutarch Against Colotes. A Lesson in
History of Philosophy</em>, Oxford: Oxford University Press.</li>

<li>Martin, H. M., 2011, &ldquo;Plutarchean Morality: Arete, Tyche,
and non-Consequentialism&rdquo;, in G. Roskam and L. Van der Stockt
(eds.), 2011, <em>Virtues for the People: Aspects of Plutarchean
Ethics</em>, Leuven: Leuven University Press, 133&ndash;151.</li>

<li>Meeusen, M., 2016,, <em>Plutarch&rsquo;s Science of Natural
Problems: A Study with Commentary on &lsquo;Quaestiones
Naturales&rsquo;. Plutarchea hypomnemata</em>. Leuven: Leuven
University Press.</li>

<li>Lamberton, R., 2001, <em>Plutarch</em>, New Haven and London: Yale
University Press.</li>

<li>Lanzilotta, L., and I. Gallarte (eds.), 2012, <em>Plutarch in the
Religious and Philosophical Doiscourse of Late Antiquity</em>,
Leiden/Boston: Brill.</li>

<li>Lanza, M., 2022, &ldquo;Ammonio e Socrate: due maestri a
confronto. Figure magistrali, maestri di filosofia e norme di
educazione in Plutarco&rdquo;, <em>Anais de Filosofia
Cl&aacute;ssica</em>, 31: 1&ndash;25.</li>

<li>Nesselrath, H.G., 2010, <em>Plutarch, On the daimonion of
Socrates</em>, T&uuml;bingen: Mohr Siebeck.</li>

<li>Nikolaidis, A. G., 2011, &ldquo;Plutarch&rsquo;s Minor Ethics:
Some Remarks on <em>De garrulitate</em>, <em>De curiositate</em>, and
<em>De vitioso pudore</em>&rdquo;, in G. Roskam and L. Van der Stockt
(eds.), <em>Virtues for the People: Aspects of Plutarchean
Ethics</em>, Leuven: Leuven University Press, 205&ndash;222.</li>

<li>O&rsquo;Brien, C. S., 2015, <em>The Demiurge in Ancient
Thought</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press.</li>

<li>Opsomer, J., 1994, &ldquo;L&rsquo;&acirc;me du monde et
l&rsquo;&acirc;me de l&rsquo;homme chez Plutarque,&rdquo; in M. G.
Vald&eacute;s (ed.), <em>Studios sobre Plutarco: ideas
religiosas.</em> <em>Actas del III Simposio Internacional sobre
Plutarco</em>, Madrid, 33&ndash;49.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1997, &ldquo;Favorinus versus Epictetus on
the philosophical heritage of Plutarch. A Debate on
Epistemology,&rdquo; in J. Mossman (ed.), <em>Plutarch and his
Intellectual World</em>, London-Swansea, 17&ndash;40.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 1999, In <em>Search of the Truth. Academic
Tendencies in Middle Platonism</em>, Leuven.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2001, &ldquo;Neoplatonist criticisms of
Plutarch,&rdquo; in A. P&eacute;rez Jimenez (ed.), <em>Estudios sobre
Plutarco. Misticismo y religiones mist&eacute;ricas en la obra de
Plutarco. Actas del VII Simposio espa&ntilde;ol sobre Plutarco</em>,
Madrid, 187&ndash;200.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2005, &ldquo;Demiurges in Early Imperial
Platonism,&rdquo; in R. Hirsch-Luipold (ed.), <em>Gott und G&ouml;tter
bei Plutarch</em>, Berlin/New York: Walter de Gruyter,
51&ndash;99.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2007, &ldquo;The place of Plutarch in the
history of Platonism,&rdquo; in P. V. Cacciatore and F. Ferrari (ed.),
<em>Plutarch e la cultura della sua et&agrave;</em>, Napoli
281&ndash;309.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2009, &ldquo;M. Annius Ammonius, A
Philosophical Profile, &rdquo; in M. Bonazzi and J. Opsomer (ed.),
<em>The Origins of the Platonic System. Platonisms of the Early Empire
and their Philosophical Contexts</em>,
Louvain&ndash;Namur&ndash;Paris&ndash;Walpole: Editions Peeters,
123&ndash;186.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Virtue, Fortune, Happiness in
Theory and Practice&rdquo;, in G. Roskam and L. Van der Stockt (eds.),
<em>Virtues for the People: Aspects of Plutarchean Ethics</em>,
Leuven: Leuven University Press, 151&ndash;173.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2023, &ldquo;In the Spirit of Plato&rdquo;,
in F. B. Titchener and A. V. Zadorojnyi (eds.), <em>The Cambridge
Companion to Plutarch</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press,
79&ndash;100.</li>

<li>Pade, M. 2023, &ldquo;Plutarch in the Italian Renaissance&rdquo;,
in F. B. Titchener and A. V. Zadorojnyi (eds.), <em>The Cambridge
Companion to Plutarch</em>, Cambridge: Cambridge University Press,
323&ndash;339</li>

<li>Petrucci, F., 2015a, &ldquo;Argumentative Strategies in the
&lsquo;Platonic Section&rsquo; of Plutarch&rsquo;s <em>De Iside et
Osiride</em> (chapters 45&ndash;64)&rdquo;, <em>Mnemosyne</em>, 69:
226&ndash;48.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash; 2015b, &ldquo;Plutarch&rsquo;s Theory of
Cosmological Powers in the <em>De Iside et Osiride&rdquo;</em>,
<em>Apeiron</em>, 49: 329&ndash;67.</li>

<li>Roskam, G., 2007, <em>A Commentary on Plutarch&rsquo;s De Latenter
Vivendo</em>, Leuven: Leuven University Press.</li>

<li>&ndash;&ndash;&ndash;, 2011, &ldquo;Aristotle in Middle Platonism.
The Case of Plutarch of Chaeronea&rdquo; in T. B&eacute;natouil, E.
Maffi, and F. Trabattoni (eds.), <em>Plato, Aristotle, or both?
